46:07.000 --> 46:10.000
Personality and self-perception

46:11.000 --> 46:17.000
So, now we will get acquainted with the concept of self-perception and feedback,

46:18.000 --> 46:25.000
and what psychological institutions are at the heart of the perception of one individual over another.

46:26.000 --> 46:28.000
So, what is personal perception?

46:29.000 --> 46:35.000
Personal perception is the obtaining and processing of information about one subject over another.

46:35.000 --> 46:43.000
As an object and a subject of information, both individual and a group of people can act.

46:44.000 --> 46:52.000
However, the complexity of the process of perception is that the ability of a person to process information is not limitless.

46:53.000 --> 46:59.000
When forming the image of a partner, a person encounters a certain amount of fragmentary information,

46:59.000 --> 47:07.000
that is, with pieces of information, and evaluates them taking into account personal psychological and emotional institutions.

47:08.000 --> 47:16.000
The entire restlessness of information in these fragments is built up by a person based on his personal subjective experience.

47:17.000 --> 47:21.000
Thus, information distortion occurs.

47:22.000 --> 47:28.000
Now I will demonstrate to you what the distortion of information looks like on a small game.

47:29.000 --> 47:30.000
