50:22.000 --> 50:30.000
Thus, a psychological phenomenon called openness is of great importance for mutual understanding.

50:31.000 --> 50:32.000
What is openness?

50:33.000 --> 50:39.000
Openness is a psychological phenomenon that depends on the level of awareness of one's inner self

50:40.000 --> 50:43.000
and self-perception at the personal level.

50:44.000 --> 50:52.000
It should be remembered that an inadequate idea of ​​one's own self creates many psychological barriers to communication.

50:53.000 --> 50:58.000
But the conditions for forming an adequate idea of ​​one's own personality

50:59.000 --> 51:04.000
are its perception and analysis of one's behavior from the point of view of others.

51:05.000 --> 51:08.000
The process of receiving feedback in interaction,

51:08.000 --> 51:11.000
based on which the image of one's own self is formed,

51:12.000 --> 51:17.000
can be demonstrated on the model created by Joseph Loft and Harry Ingham,

51:18.000 --> 51:23.000
which is now called the Johari window in psychology and sociology.

51:24.000 --> 51:28.000
What is the Johari window and what does it look like?

51:29.000 --> 51:32.000
The Johari window consists of four squares,

51:32.000 --> 51:42.000
each of which represents a definition of a person's awareness in society and awareness of a person himself.

51:43.000 --> 51:46.000
Please pay attention to the slide.

51:47.000 --> 51:52.000
There are two lines in the Johari window, horizontal and vertical.

51:53.000 --> 52:00.000
In this case, the vertical line divides the Johari window into two parts, the right and the left.

52:01.000 --> 52:05.000
The left part, the blue one on your slide,

52:06.000 --> 52:10.000
is all the information that a person knows about himself,

52:11.000 --> 52:14.000
that is, his open zone and his hidden zone.

52:15.000 --> 52:17.000
But the orange part, the right part,

52:18.000 --> 52:22.000
is all the information that a person does not know about himself,

52:23.000 --> 52:26.000
that is, his blind zone and his unknown zone.

52:27.000 --> 52:29.000
Also, along the horizontal line,

52:30.000 --> 52:34.000
only here we have the lower part of the Johari window and the upper part of the Johari window.

52:35.000 --> 52:38.000
The lower part of the window represents the information

52:39.000 --> 52:43.000
that a person does not know about himself, society or group,

52:44.000 --> 52:47.000
that is, his hidden zone and unknown zone.

52:48.000 --> 52:51.000
And, accordingly, the upper part along the horizontal line

52:51.000 --> 52:55.000
is the information that a group knows about a person,

52:56.000 --> 52:58.000
that is, his open zone and his blind zone.

52:59.000 --> 53:03.000
Thus, let's consider each zone separately.

53:04.000 --> 53:06.000
So, zone number one is open.

53:07.000 --> 53:09.000
This is information about an individual, about a person,

53:10.000 --> 53:13.000
known to him or herself and to others.

53:15.000 --> 53:19.000
It is quite clear that the larger the open zone,

53:19.000 --> 53:23.000
the more trust relationships are established.

53:25.000 --> 53:29.000
Zone number two is the so-called blind zone.

53:30.000 --> 53:33.000
This is information about a person, which is known to other people,

53:34.000 --> 53:36.000
but unknown to him or herself.

53:37.000 --> 53:40.000
That is, it is the opinion of others about a Personality.

53:41.000 --> 53:44.000
Here is the following situation.

53:44.000 --> 53:50.000
If the opinion of others about me coincides with my idea of ​​myself,

53:51.000 --> 53:58.000
I have good and normal relations with these people or with a group of these people.

53:59.000 --> 54:05.000
If the opinion of others does not coincide with my idea of ​​myself,

54:06.000 --> 54:07.000
but is somewhat subdued,

54:08.000 --> 54:11.000
there are likely conflicts and, in general,

54:11.000 --> 54:13.000
there are likely to be no relations at all.

54:14.000 --> 54:20.000
If the opinion of others is somewhat subdued with my own assessment of myself,

54:21.000 --> 54:23.000
I perceive it as a leap.

54:24.000 --> 54:29.000
It should be noted that everything related to the blind zone

54:30.000 --> 54:33.000
